Happy Trad Anniversary to my Igbo Prince Charming!👑🇳🇬
Thank you baby for not only welcoming me into your beautiful culture, but allowing me to lovingly embrace this very part of you and your family. I absolutely love being apart of the littest culture on earth! And I love that my little Naija girl was born ready for a money spray💸 

Being in a dual cultured home only brings more wealth of life experiences and history, respect for values, and we have found more in common than we ever thought — especially being that we grew up across the world from one another. 

And a special thank you to all of my Naija family, and our friends that embrace me as your own. Y’all have taught me so well that my dancing was so good people in Enugu really believe I’m from the East! And I’m not correcting them O!😝💃🏽

Each Contestant has $20 to make an entree of their choice, 30 minutes to shop, and 1 hour to cook!

Today is the Day I begin my 10 week journey to fight against Blood Cancer 💪🏾🩸 I’m so honored to have been chosen to fight this fight in honor of my Dad, who lost his battle with Leukemia when I was only 15 years old. 💔

While I plan to honor Dad in this very special way, I hope to bring about awareness, patient advocacy, treatment, and the triumph of incredible survivors I’ve met along the way that have benefited from the work of the Leukemia and Lymphoma Society. @llstexasgulfcoast is doing incredible, groundbreaking things, but they can’t do it without our help!

So hop in, we are Fighting Cancer!💪🏾🩸In just a short 10 weeks, I have a big task to raise as much money as possible to help patients and research efforts, and I can’t be more nervously excited for the task, but I’m going to give it all I’ve got — and I hope you will join me. I love you guys — Together, We are #TougherThanCancer!❤️💪🏾 

So I ask, that you please Donate, Share my posts, and Tell a Friend to Tell a Friend! I appreciate you all more than you know! Link in bio!! Let’s go!! ❤️💪🏾

Well, we have officially begun our fight to end blood cancer!! 🩸💪🏾

I am humbled by this opportunity to raise awareness and funds for The Leukemia & Lymphoma Society and I am determined to get current and future patients the resources they need to fight this!

I have a big goal, but we are off to a great start!! A HUGE thank you to those of you who have already donated, shared my story, reposted, liked, or simply just thought about this wild ride I’m on! ❤️❤️ I’m already so overwhelmed with gratitude for you guys for joining me🥹🙏🏾

I’ve received so much feedback from patients, survivors, and families that I didn’t know were faced with Cancer. And that reminds me that our work is not in vain and we are making a difference by helping people fight this terrible battle 🥹💪🏾 You are not alone, and together, we are TOUGHER THAN CANCER!!💪🏾

So I hope you will support me! I have 10 short weeks to raise as much money as possible, and kick cancer’s butt!💪🏾 

I love you guys SO much!!! 💪🏾🥹❤️

I chose to get out of my comfort zone and fight for something I believe in, so last night @51fifteen hosted my Kickoff Toast for my fight against Blood Cancer as I begin my 10-week fundraising campaign! 

I had the honor of having @never_parrish speak at my first event, and we all left inspired and motivated to do more for Heroes like her and millions others fighting cancer. 

Thank you @51fifteen for hosting such a fabulous event — the food and service was more than incredible 🤍 

And a huge thank you to all of my family and friends that came to support me 🥹 I’m wayyy out of my comfort zone in this, but you all make me feel empowered to do my best to make an impact. 

Week 1 is officially off to a fantastic start!🎉 Thank you all for donating, it means so much to me! We still have so much work to do to reach our goal, but we got this! More exciting ways to give and participate to come — so get in guys, we are kicking cancer’s butt!!💪🏾

The past 10 weeks of fundraising all came down to last night!! And I am blown away at how much of an impact we made… 

WE RAISED A GRAND TOTAL OF $188,000🎉❤️IN 10 WEEKS!?!🎉🥹🤯 

I am so so proud of what we accomplished! As a candidacy class, we raised a total of $1,319,083 towards the fight to end blood cancer!💪🏾❤️

I won 1st Runner Up in this incredible race and won the Mission Award for Advocacy for @llstexasgulfcoast 🎉😆🥹Congratulations to Our Visionary of the Year @lauranelsonpersia!🎉We connected instantly in this journey, and knowing your story and your fight to get here makes me feel like I won too! We raised this money for warriors like you!! I love you, I’m proud of you and I’m so happy to have gained a true friend! 🥹❤️

Team Tougher Than Cancer - how do I even thank you?! We raised SO much money, had events, giveaways, and through it all you guys were there.🥹 Lending me encouragement, support, your time and money. Thank you to my top Team Members, Stanley, my sister Cissy, and @juliawang_htx who each individually raised over $20,000🎉🤯🥹 and a Special Thank you to my entire Team!! You guys mean the world to me: @oscar.c.o @emisha.o @bjthomas02 @qtpie81886, @jemimasway @terynlouisa @rich_i_am Morris, Toni,@swardally, @theprettyartist @corischerer @qui_soulpretty @madzbub @sariahkhalil 

And a special thank you to @llstexasgulfcoast @laurenepaine for selecting me for this incredible journey🥹❤️ I couldn’t have done this without you @christina_renee3 @never_parrish ❤️

And to all of You guys!! Thank you from the bottom of my heart for helping me honor my Dad in such an incredibly special way🥹❤️ Though he may have lost his battle here on earth, we continued the fight for him here so that another family won’t have to share the same fate❤️ 

Cancer didn’t win this time, because we are TOUGHER THAN CANCER ❤️💪🏾 

#LLSVisionaries

Honestly, I don’t even know where to begin 🥹🫶🏾 I’ve finally come down from the longest and shortest 10 weeks of fundraising, and really soaked in what we accomplished in this short time. The impact we made. The lives we touched — and it’s nothing short of a God moment. I feel so honored that God used me in this way to help lives like Manny, who got diagnosed with Acute Myleoid Leukemia at the age of 2, and now stands as the vibrant cancer-free 13 year old you see so handsomely standing with me 🥹👏🏾

It’s because of the work that @llstexasgulfcoast is doing — the research, the patient advocacy, the fundraising. It ALL matters, because there are millions of patients that rely on it for survival and I’m just happy to be a small part of the pie that helped make it happen. 

I told you guys this was for my Dad, and you guys supported me all the way. At times I felt like a crazy Mary Kay Lady trying to get a pink Cadillac 😂 but you guys showered me with love, encouragement, support and donations to make this one of the most God fulfilling moments of my life. We raised over $190,000 and I received so much more than I ever realized in this experience. 

To my Mom — The Caregiver ❤️ who did the final act of love for my Dad so beautifully and heroically. Mom I love you so so much and I’m so happy that we got to accomplish this for Daddy together side by side. 

Team Tougher Than Cancer didn’t even fit into my last picture because there was so many of us lol, but it only makes sense because how can I even capture the love and support you all gave me — it could fill the ocean 🫶🏾 Thank you all so very much for all your time, effort and support. 

If there was one take away, it’s from one of the most remarkable women I’ve met in this race @never_parrish ❤️ “You can choose courage or comfort, but you can’t choose both.” And I pray that we all choose courage every single time because there’s something so rewarding on the other side ❤️ 

Daddy, Thank you for being the best Angel in the sky, for watching over us the way you do. I wish you were there, but I know you had the best seat in the house. I love you forever and I hope I made you proud #TougherThanCancer❤️💪🏾
@llstexasgulfcoast Visionary of the Year Grand Finale 🩸 Congratulations to our girl @charlyelynne! 😍 You did that!! 👏🏼🎉❤️ #TeamTougherThanCancer
Beyond being the love of my life, watching you as the best Daddy is my favorite role you play. Happy Father’s Day, We love you so much 🤍

My journey with the Leukemia & Lymphoma Society had been one of the most life-changing, purposeful tasks I’ve ever been blessed with. Our team completed the fundraiser with a Grand Total of $198,000 that will go towards research and funding for Blood Cancer patients❤️

The most special moment has been the opportunity to dedicate a $100,000 Grant in honor of my Father, Charles E. Nichols in the fight against Chronic Myeloid Leukemia, so that another patient faced with the same disease will fight and WIN their battle. 

I dedicated another $50,000 Grant to the Dare to Dream Project, an @llsusa initiative to end childhood cancer by providing safe, non-toxic successful treatments for our littlest of warriors. I named this Grant in honor of my beautiful friend @qui_soulpretty son, Malachi Preston, a Lymphoma Survivor and a representation of the millions of kids all over the world that are faced with blood cancer, the #1 form of childhood cancer. 

To add the cherry on top of our successful campaign, @llsusa and @llstexasgulfcoast invited all candidates around the nation who raised over $150,000 to NYC to attend a Research Gathering to meet with the world’s Top Research Scientists and Doctors who are dedicated to developing and revolutionizing treatment options and medicine that will ultimately #CancelCancer! To sit in the room with these brilliant minds and hear their passion and determination to cure patients all over the world brought tears to my eyes. 

While my Dad may have missed the opportunity to receive these groundbreaking options, I am so overwhelmed with joy and gratitude that future patients will not share the same fate. 

If you, or anyone you know, is battling cancer just know there are brilliant scientists passionately working towards your cure. I witnessed firsthand their love and passion for you and they won’t stop until it’s done. This whole journey has been an emotionally amazing experience and I wouldn’t be here without all of you all. So thank you for allowing me to advocate and get these funds to the people that need it the most to save the lives of those we love. Together, we will always be #TougherThanCancer ❤️💪🏾
